-- 53. NUMERIC FUNCTIONS

-- Sql has a lot of built in functions in order to deal with data.


1. ROUND() Function

-- This function will round off the data passed to it.
-- It will round the data off to the precision of the second argument which is optional.

--Select round(5.4994,2);
-- Result :- 5.50

2. TRUNCATE() Function

-- It is used for removing the digits from a number after the precision points

-- Select TRUNCATE(2.95434,2);
-- Result = 2.95


3. CEILING() Function and FLOOR() Function

-- Select Ceiling(5.2);  -- returns the smallest integer which is just greater than the given value
-- Result :- 6

-- Select Floor(5.7);    -- return the largest digit which is just smaller than the given value.
-- Result :- 5

4.ABS() Function 
-- Always return an absolute value i.e. +value as result, whether we pass +ve or -ve.

-- Select ABS(5.2);
-- Result :- 5.2

-- Select ABS(-5.2);
-- Result:- 5.2


5. RAND() Function

-- Produces a random floating point number between 0 and 1.
--SELECT RAND();

-- Result:- 0.123456   or Result:- 0.456789
